</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,410,1220]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,330,410,436]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Identification:</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<quantity box="[541,671,410,436]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="19.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="18.0">18–21 mm</quantity>
. Foretibia in male covered with thick long scales giving a bushy appearance. Overall ground color of forewing is light brown with a slight ferruginous cast and no obvious striping. Antemedial line is present, but faint and consists of a slightly curved vertical line within the discal cell and a second line between the Cu and A veins. Postmedial line consists of a double row of black spots with the distal row consisting of more spots than the proximal row. In some specimens the spots from the proximal row are connected with short lines to the spots in the distal row forming a zig-zag pattern. The orbicular and reniform spots are cream colored and the reniform can have a small ground color spot in its ventral half. Terminal line is a series of minute black spots, which can be absent in some specimens. Hindwing is gray, lighter basally with no distinct darker margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,410,1220]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee False Wainscot" authorityYear="1852" box="[196,468,746,771]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Leucania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudargyria">
<emphasis box="[196,468,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Leucania pseudargyria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[624,731,746,771]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Leucania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ursula">
<emphasis box="[624,731,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. ursula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the male foretibia having thick, long scales giving it a bushy appearance. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee False Wainscot" authorityYear="1852" box="[375,647,784,809]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Leucania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudargyria">
<emphasis box="[375,647,784,809]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Leucania pseudargyria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is larger with a forewing length of 
<quantity box="[1062,1188,784,810]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="19.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="18.0">18–21 mm</quantity>
versus 
<quantity box="[1279,1405,784,810]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="15.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="13.0">13–17 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,257,821,846]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Leucania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ursula">
<emphasis box="[151,257,821,846]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. ursula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The forewing ground color in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee False Wainscot" authorityYear="1852" box="[628,814,821,846]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Leucania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudargyria">
<emphasis box="[628,814,821,846]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. pseudargyria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is light brown with a distinct ferruginous cast and in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,257,858,883]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Leucania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ursula">
<emphasis box="[151,257,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">L. ursula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the ground color is gray with a brownish cast.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,410,1220]" box="[196,647,895,922]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,369,895,921]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Flight period:</emphasis>
